# Performance & Accessibility (Lighthouse 95+)

## Constraints

- **Measurement First:** Avoid premature optimization. Identify specific bottlenecks via profiling (DevTools Performance tab) before applying any fixes.
- **Performance Budgets:**
  - **Core Web Vitals:** LCP ≤ 2.5s, INP ≤ 200ms, CLS ≤ 0.1.
  - **Bundle Size:** Keep initial feature chunks < 50kb. Use `next/dynamic` for heavy, non-critical dependencies. Use `pnpm analyze` to inspect the bundle.
- **LCP Optimization:** Use the `priority` attribute on the first visible `next/image`, or the hero asset.
- **Image Standards:** Always use `next/image` with explicit `width`/`height` (or `fill`) to prevent CLS.
- **Icon & Font Strategy:** Use tree-shakable icons (`lucide-react`). Fonts are loaded via `next/font` with `display: "swap"` (see `src/app/layout.tsx`).
- **A11y SSOT:** All interactive elements MUST have an `aria-label`, `role`, or associated `<label>`. Maintain WCAG AA compliance (4.5:1 contrast ratio).
- **Skeletons:** Reserve layout space with `Skeleton` (`@/ui`) for any content that loads asynchronously — see `ui-components.mdc`.

## Bans

- **Layout Shift:** Forbidden to render async content without reserved dimensions (use Skeletons).
- **Native `<img>`:** Forbidden — use `next/image`.
- **Blocking JS:** Forbidden to load heavy third-party scripts on the main thread (use `next/script` with an appropriate `strategy`).
- **A11y Gaps:** Forbidden to use `div`/`span` as a button without `tabIndex`/`onKeyDown`/`role="button"` — use `@/ui` `Button` instead.
- **Alt Text:** Forbidden to leave `alt` attributes empty or generic (e.g., `"image"`).

## Correct Implementation

<example>
```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

export function Hero() {
  return (
    <section>
      <h1>Ship faster</h1>
      <Image src="/hero.webp" alt="Dashboard analytics overview" width={1200} height={600} priority />
      <Button aria-label="Start free trial">Get started</Button>
    </section>
  );
}
```
</example>

## Incorrect Implementation

<incorrect-example>
```tsx
const BadHero = () => (
  <div>
    <img src="/hero.png" />
    <div onClick={handleAction}>Click here</div>
  </div>
);
```
</incorrect-example>
